{
  "texts": [
    "ViT-L's superior accuracy (NC4 = 0.876) despite inferior geometry (NC2 = 0.541) is consistent with ViT-L relying more on parameter capacity than on efficient representation.",
    "The hub marginalization pattern is closely aligned with the Information Scrambling Index (Section 4): ViT-S's collapsed scrambling (down to approximately -0.001) is associated with incomplete marginalization (CCC = 0.018), ViT-B's controlled scrambling (roughly 0.004 to 0.009) is associated with more complete marginalization (CCC = 0.004), while ViT-L's excessive scrambling (up to approximately 0.031) is accompanied by unstable marginalization.",
    "This relationship suggests that scrambling and marginalization are complementary views of the same underlying reorganization, redistributing information away from the architectural hub into a distributed patch-token consensus.",
    "Our findings highlight an inefficiency in this regime: the [CLS] token tends to become a bottleneck that trained models effectively bypass.",
    "In our ImageNet ViTs, ViT-B enters a low-hub regime (CCC ≲ 0.005) by about layer 9, whereas ViT-L does not reach comparable marginalization until roughly layer 17, using almost twice as many blocks for a worse final geometry."
  ]
}